	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You draw a circle on the ground by pointing with your finger. Glowing softly, it magically compels truth from those standing within it.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><p>You create a magical zone that guards against deception. Only you know where the circle is, or who is affected. All affected creatures instantly know what the spell is doing to them.</p><p><strong>[[/save charisma]]{Charisma Save}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target cannot say things it believes are untrue while in the circle.</p><ul><li class=\"obanQ\" dir=\"auto\" id=\"shp4g22219\"><p class=\"yN-vL dTQTo\" id=\"x6ucm22220\">If the target tries to lie or deliberately mislead someone into believing something untrue, their words make no sound. </p></li><li class=\"obanQ\" dir=\"auto\" id=\"jmvza22601\"><p class=\"yN-vL dTQTo\" id=\"bvse122602\">The spell does not force people to speak, but it can prevent lies.</p></li><li class=\"obanQ\" dir=\"auto\" id=\"wxlvk22249\"><p class=\"yN-vL dTQTo\" id=\"b8ml922250\">This spell only affects spoken language, and not gestures or written or sign language.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> No effect, and you know the target resisted the effect.</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> The zone remains in place. Targets roll a save when they enter for the first time.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
